ceo_chair_split,roa_eat,3,review,1,Direction is context-dependent: CEO duality negative during crisis; CEO-chair separation positive in ESG-performance models. Staggered boards (related to CEO entrenchment) associated with ROA drops in non-competitive industries,GOV-012,yes,"[audit:G] modify/low/paper_verified=partial: The relationship between CEO duality/chair split and ROA is verified as context-dependent in retrieved papers (chunk d58cec54: CEO duality negative during crisis; chunk 275ca64e: antitakeover legislation → ~0.8% drop in return on capital), but the direction is genuinely mixed and the evidence base is heterogeneous — crisis-period banking studies vs. natural experiments on antitakeover statutes.; MOD: Retain as ceo_chair_split → roa_eat (positive direction: separation improves ROA) but assign very low confidence weight. Encode as crisis-conditional and industry-conditional. Flag that the evidence base conflates CEO duality with antitakeover entrenchment mechanisms. Treat as a soft, directional prior only — not a strong forbidden-edge constraint."
