iso_14001_exists,net_profit_margin,3,review,1,"Firms that implemented the EMS certification get an EBITDA and a Net Income (our measures of profitability) 11% and 24.6% higher, respectively, than firms without EMS certification.",22db0374-b69a-41f3-a3a5-95b76ab8dea1,yes,"[audit:E] modify/medium/paper_verified=yes: Paper 22db0374 is verified and explicitly states 'firms that implemented the EMS certification get an EBITDA and a Net Income (our measures of profitability) 11% and 24.6% higher, respectively, than firms without EMS certification'; however, the paper measures net income and EBITDA, not net profit margin (net income/revenue), and the sample is limited to Brazilian firms.; MOD: Remap effect variable from net_profit_margin to net_profit_absolute or note that the paper measures net income levels; add caveat that this is a Brazilian-specific finding with potential self-selection bias; the positive direction is supported but the variable mapping is imprecise."
