emission_reduction_policy_score,tobins_q,3,review,1,King and Lenox (2002): Lower emissions (in t) are significantly associated with higher financial performance (in t+1). Significant and positive relationship of waste prevention with ROA and Tobin's q. Hart and Ahuja (1996): Pollution prevention activities have a positive influence on financial performance within 1-2 years. ROE takes longer to be affected. Russo and Fouts (1997): Positive and significant impact of environmental performance on ROA.,b52a324f-b7a8-4def-8442-c6462110aa2a,no,"[audit:E] no/high/paper_verified=yes: Paper b52a324f cites King & Lenox (2002) finding a positive relationship between waste prevention and Tobin's Q; however, paper 30ecac5c/de47cf17 explicitly states 'carbon emissions reduction does not influence the stock market performance in terms of Tobin's Q' — the primary paper directly contradicts the proposed constraint."
scope_3_emissions_tco2e,tobins_q,3,review,1,Log total carbon (Scope 1): 0.081*** (2.974); Log total carbon (Scope 2): 0.091*** (2.731); Log total carbon (Scope 3): 0.297*** (3.661). Log carbon intensity (Scope 1): -0.004 (-0.170); Log carbon intensity (Scope 2): -0.041 (-1.338).,0bc1c1a7-ff3b-43a1-b2cb-397cfc89a5c6,no,"[audit:E] no/high/paper_verified=yes: Paper 0bc1c1a7 shows a positive coefficient for log total Scope 3 (0.297***), which contradicts the expected negative direction; papers 5da255ba and 4a4ac51c explicitly state 'we found no such effect for Scope 2 and Scope 3'; paper f7e75bfc finds Scope 3 positive but not significant (p=0.090); the positive coefficient in 0bc1c1a7 likely reflects scale effects (larger firms emit more Scope 3 and have higher market cap)."
shareholder_rights_score,market_value_equity,3,review,1,Short-term gains reversed by year 3 (Popadak); antitakeover statutes reduce ROA especially in non-competitive industries; innovation (patents) decreases 11–16% under antitakeover protection; staggered boards declined from 60% to 12% of S&P 500 (2000–2013); dual-class shares preserve founder control at expense of minority shareholders,GOV-018,yes,"[audit:G] modify/medium/paper_verified=yes: The causal relationship between shareholder rights/governance proposals and market value is verified via regression discontinuity evidence (chunk 39e2a9f1: Cuñat, Gine & Guadalupe — votes removing anti-takeover provisions yield significant positive returns; chunk f62faa04: antitakeover legislation → ~0.8% drop in return on capital), but the direction is time-horizon dependent — short-term positive gains are reversed by year 3 (chunk fcad1888: Popadak), and staggered board evidence is contested (chunk 85088b34: time-series analysis finds staggered boards positively related to firm value).; MOD: Retain as shareholder_rights_score → market_value_equity (positive direction: stronger rights → higher market value) but encode as: short-term positive effect only (reverses by year 3); contested in time-series analysis; identification-strategy dependent. Treat as a weak-to-moderate short-term constraint. Flag that long-run effect may be negative or null."
